SIMPLE: penetrative
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Penetrative
<hw>Pen"e*tra*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧n⟦eacute⟧tratif</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Tending to
penetrate; of a penetrating quality; piercing; <as>as, the
<ex>penetrative</ex> sun</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His look became keen and <qex>penetrative</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hawthorne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having the power to affect or impress the mind or
heart; impressive; <as>as, <ex>penetrative</ex> shame</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Acute; discerning; sagacious; <as>as,
<ex>penetrative</ex> wisdom</as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The
<xex>penetrative</xex> eye.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Wordsworth.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Led on by skill of <qex>penetrative</qex> soul.</q>
<rj><qau>Grainger.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Penetrativeness</ent>⟦br⟧
